    grammar_explanation: '"Can" expresses ability (I can swim = I know how) or permission (Can I go?). "Can\'t" / "cannot" is the negative. The verb after "can" is always in base form — no "to", no "-s". Questions: move "can" to front: "Can you speak English?"',
    grammar_explanation_tr: '"Can" yetenek (I can swim = biliyorum) veya izin (Can I go?) ifade eder. "Can\'t" / "cannot" olumsuzdur. "Can"den sonraki fiil her zaman yalın haldedir — "to" veya "-s" eklenmez. Soru: "can" başa gelir: "Can you speak English?"',
    examples: ['I can swim.', 'She can\'t drive.', 'Can you help me?', 'He can speak three languages.', 'Can I open the window?', 'They can\'t come today.'],
