    grammar_explanation: '"Want to" expresses desire (I want to eat). "Need to" expresses necessity (I need to go). "Would like to" is the polite version of "want to" (I\'d like to order, please). All three are followed by "to + verb".',
    grammar_explanation_tr: '"Want to" istek ifade eder (I want to eat). "Need to" zorunluluk ifade eder (I need to go). "Would like to" ise "want to"nun kibar halidir (I\'d like to order, please). Üçü de "to + fiil" ile devam eder.',
    examples: ['I want to learn English.', 'She needs to study.', 'I\'d like to order a coffee, please.', 'Do you want to come?', 'He doesn\'t need to worry.', 'Would you like to sit down?'],
