    grammar_explanation: 'Some verbs are followed by gerund (-ing): enjoy, finish, avoid, mind, suggest. Some by infinitive (to + verb): want, need, decide, hope, plan. Some take both with different meanings: "stop doing" = cease, "stop to do" = pause in order to do. Must memorize which verbs take which.',
    grammar_explanation_tr: 'Bazı fiiller isim-fiil (-ing) ile devam eder: enjoy, finish, avoid, mind, suggest. Bazıları mastar (to + fiil) ile: want, need, decide, hope, plan. Bazıları ikisini de alır farklı anlamlarla. Hangi fiilin hangisini aldığı ezberlenmelidir.',
    examples: ['I enjoy reading books.', 'She wants to travel.', 'He finished eating.', 'We decided to stay.', 'Stop talking!', 'I need to sleep.'],
