    description: 'More sophisticated sentence linking',
    lesson_type: 'grammar', grammar_pattern: 'Although + clause / However, ... / Moreover, ... / Therefore, ...',
    grammar_explanation: '"Although" = despite the fact that (Although it was cold, we went out). "However" = but (more formal, starts a new sentence). "Moreover" / "Furthermore" = in addition. "Therefore" = as a result. These make your writing and speech more sophisticated.',
    grammar_explanation_tr: '"Although" = buna rağmen (Although it was cold, we went out). "However" = ancak (daha resmi, yeni cümle başlatır). "Moreover" = ayrıca, üstelik. "Therefore" = bu nedenle. Bunlar konuşma ve yazıyı daha gelişmiş yapar.',
    examples: ['Although it was raining, we went for a walk.', 'The test was hard. However, I passed.', 'She speaks English. Moreover, she speaks French.', 'He was sick. Therefore, he stayed home.', 'I like the job, although the pay is low.', 'The food was good. Furthermore, it was cheap.'],
