    grammar_explanation: '"So" goes before an adjective alone: "It\'s SO cold." "Such" goes before (a/an +) adjective + noun: "She\'s SUCH a nice person." / "They are SUCH good friends." Both express emphasis or degree. Can be followed by "that": "It was so hot that we stayed inside."',
    grammar_explanation_tr: '"So" tek başına sıfattan önce gelir: "It\'s SO cold." "Such" (a/an +) sıfat + isimden önce gelir: "She\'s SUCH a nice person." İkisi de vurgulama veya derece ifade eder. "that" ile devam edebilir: "It was so hot that we stayed inside."',
    examples: ['It\'s so cold today!', 'She is such a nice person.', 'The movie was so boring.', 'They are such good friends.', 'It was so hot that we went swimming.', 'He is such a talented musician.'],
