    grammar_explanation: '"Going to" expresses PLANNED intentions and PREDICTIONS based on evidence. Plans: "I\'m going to travel next week." (I decided already). Predictions: "Look at those clouds — it\'s going to rain." (I can see evidence). Not for spontaneous decisions (use "will" for those).',
    grammar_explanation_tr: '"Going to" PLANLANMIŞ niyetleri ve kanıta dayalı TAHMİNLERİ ifade eder. Planlar: "I\'m going to travel next week." (çoktan karar verdim). Tahminler: "Look at those clouds — it\'s going to rain." (kanıt görüyorum).',
    examples: ['I\'m going to study abroad next year.', 'She\'s going to have a baby.', 'Look at those clouds — it\'s going to rain.', 'We\'re going to move to a new house.', 'Are you going to come to the party?', 'They\'re not going to like this.'],
