    grammar_explanation: '"Will" expresses spontaneous decisions, promises, offers, and general predictions. Decision made NOW: "I\'ll have the chicken." Promise: "I will call you." Offer: "I\'ll help you." Prediction (no evidence): "I think it will rain tomorrow." Negative: "won\'t".',
    grammar_explanation_tr: '"Will" anlık kararları, vaatleri, teklifleri ve genel tahminleri ifade eder. Şimdi verilen karar: "I\'ll have the chicken." Vaat: "I will call you." Teklif: "I\'ll help you." Tahmin (kanıtsız): "I think it will rain tomorrow." Olumsuz: "won\'t".',
    examples: ['I\'ll have the chicken, please.', 'I will call you tomorrow.', 'Don\'t worry, I\'ll help you.', 'She won\'t come to the party.', 'Will you marry me?', 'I think it will rain tomorrow.'],
