    lesson_type: 'grammar', grammar_pattern: 'Going to = planned / Will = spontaneous/promise/offer',
    grammar_explanation: '"Going to" = decided BEFORE the moment of speaking (I\'m going to buy a car — I\'ve been saving money). "Will" = decided at the moment of speaking (Oh, the phone\'s ringing — I\'ll answer it). Both work for predictions, but "going to" implies evidence.',
    grammar_explanation_tr: '"Going to" = konuşma anından ÖNCE karar verilmiş (I\'m going to buy a car — para biriktiriyordum). "Will" = konuşma anında karar verilmiş (Oh, telefon çalıyor — I\'ll answer it). İkisi de tahmin için çalışır ama "going to" kanıt ima eder.',
    examples: ['I\'m going to buy a car. (planned)', 'I\'ll have the salad. (decided now)', 'She\'s going to be a doctor. (her plan)', 'It will be a great party. (prediction)', 'Look out! That tree is going to fall! (evidence)', 'I\'ll lend you some money. (offer)'],
